# AGENTS.md mandatory preload

**`AGENTS.md`** is the repository operating contract. Cursor rules mirror it — if they diverge, follow **`AGENTS.md`** and fix the rule in the same PR.

## Before every task

1. Read **`AGENTS.md`** before analysis, planning, coding, refactoring, testing, or tool execution.
   - **IDE & AI quickstart** table for fast routing.
   - **§4** for CI gates and enforcement scripts.
   - **§5** for routing, auth UX, locale, and `proxy.ts`.
   - **§6** for directory shape and import rules.
   - **§7** for design system boundaries.
2. Prefer existing patterns over inventing new structures. Prefer contraction over expansion.
3. Do not introduce new architectural categories, folders, or conventions unless **`AGENTS.md`** is updated first.
4. If user instructions conflict with **`AGENTS.md`**, prefer the safer interpretation and ask for clarification.

## Non-negotiable boundaries

| Boundary | Rule |
|---|---|
| Module public door | `lib/features/<module>/index.ts` only — no deep imports across modules |
| ERP business logic | Inside `lib/features/<module>/...` only — never in `app/`, `proxy.ts`, or `lib/erp/` |
| `app/` layer | Routing, composition, page wiring only — no data/domain implementation |
| Mutations | Server Actions by default; Route Handlers only for `auth`, `cron`, `upload`, `webhooks`, `integrations`, `api/erp/<module>` |
| `proxy.ts` | Session/locale gate only — no DB, no business logic, no branching domain rules |
| Banned categories | `services`, `utils`, `helpers`, `repositories`, `controllers` — forbidden unless `AGENTS.md` updated first |
| Root cleanliness | No dumping directories at repo root or module root |
| UI primitives | `#components/ui/*` only — `radix-ui`/`@radix-ui/*`/`@base-ui/react` confined to `components/ui` (ESLint) |
| Design tokens | `@theme inline` `var(--*)` must resolve to `:root`/`.dark` definitions (validated by `check-design-contract.mjs`) |

## Cross-module import rule

- **Allowed:** `import { X } from "#features/<module>"`
- **Forbidden:** `import { X } from "#features/<module>/data/..."` (outside the same module)
- Same-module relative imports are fine; cross-module deep imports are always a violation.

## Change governance

- New architectural category → update **`AGENTS.md`** first in the same change.
- Conflict with a boundary → call it out, explain the risk, propose the closest compliant alternative.
- Treat boundary violations as blockers, not style nits.
